description: Master Thesis Project  Development of a machine learningdriven framework for distortion-aware power allocation in 6G MIMO-OFDM transmitters. The project integrates deep learning and communication theory to optimize transmit power, mitigate EVM distortion, and enhance energy efficiency under nonlinear PA constraints.

Today, I explored how to build interactive AI applications using the Gradio framework  a powerful tool that allows you to create simple, shareable web interfaces for your machine learning and Generative AI models.

A collection of deep learning models, training pipelines, experiments, and utilities built using modern machine learning frameworks. This repository includes clean, modular implementations of popular neural network architectures, along with reproducible training scripts, experiment tracking, and tools for data processing.

A lightweight and modular Model Extractor tool for loading, analyzing, and exporting machine-learning models. Supports extracting model layers, parameters, weights, metadata, and architecture summaries from frameworks like PyTorch or TensorFlow. Ideal for ML engineers who need to inspect, debug, convert, or document model structures.

AI-powered system for early stroke prediction that combines machine learning, deep learning, and explainable AI techniques. This comprehensive framework enhances predictive accuracy while ensuring clinical interpretability and fairness in healthcare applications.

Machine-Learning Guided discovery of High Entropy Perovskite oxides via oxygen vacancy Engineering. In this project, we deployed an integrated framework that combines density functional theory (DFT) calculations, machine learning (ML) and experimental validations do predict oxygen vacancy formation energies in HEPO electrocatalysts.

This project demonstrates how explainable AI and machine learning can be used to build transparent credit risk models that satisfy regulatory requirements under Basel III, IFRS 9, and OSFI's E-23 guidelines. The framework provides comprehensive model interpretability using SHAP and LIME.

BRCATranstypia: A machine learning framework for breast cancer PAM50 subtype prediction using TCGA-BRCA transcriptomic data. It integrates preprocessing, feature selection, model training (Random Forest, SVM, XGBoost), and visualization of gene expression patterns.

This repository hosts the practical work for the Artificial Intelligence Lab. It features implementations of core AI algorithms and projects in machine learning and deep learning, developed using Python and modern AI frameworks.

Comprehensive quantitative analysis of global anti-money laundering risks across 203 countries using advanced statistical methods and machine learning. Provides evidence-based policy frameworks for international AML/CFT cooperation, regional coordination strategies, and strategic intervention targeting.

A machine learning framework analyzing transportation policy impacts on urban congestion in the Philippines using Temporal Fusion Transformer models and causal inference. Features an interactive dashboard for policy simulation and includes 7,430+ observations from 12 data sources.

This project focuses on building a multi-model ransomware detection framework using both classical Machine Learning (ML) and **Deep Learning (DL) techniques.   The goal is to detect ransomware activity including zero-day variants across diverse, real-world datasets with a focus on binary (benign vs. ransomware) and family-level classification

This repository contains the implementation of a hybrid physics-machine learning framework for autonomous pH adjustment in complex buffered systems. The system combines Theoretical Titration Curve Generation modeling with active learning to enable rapid, precise pH optimization using low-cost automated hardware.

Cerebrus is an intelligent malware analysis framework designed to provide multi-layered defense against modern cyber threats. It integrates static analysis, machine learning, external threat intelligence, and explainable AI (XAI) to deliver a robust platform for detecting known and unknown malware across various file formats.

SMILE is a featurebased machine learning classification framework for eventinterval sequence data. While its primary application is medical diagnostics using Electronic Health Record data, the framework is generalisable to domains such as human activity recognition, music classification, and manufacturing telemetry.
Python SHIELD Machine Learning Framework - is a custom framework for AI/ML development compatible with Cuda, XPU and CPU. It also supports DDP.

TensorFlow is an open-source machine learning framework developed by Google. It provides strong support for various platforms, especially Linux, and is widely adopted in the industry due to its active community and production-ready capabilities.

This project implements a Supervised Machine Learning (ML) framework to accurately predict the cost of an Electric Vehicle (EV) based on its key features and specifications. This is fundamentally a regression problem, aiming to determine a continuous value (price) from a set of input variables (features).

The clients are able to create datasets, train different models, evaluate their metrics and inference with them. Mainly over the salary from a Undergraduate/Postgraduate/Phd students.

AI-VAPT is an autonomous, AI-driven Vulnerability Assessment & Penetration Testing (VAPT) framework designed to revolutionize cybersecurity testing. The platform combines traditional manual VAPT methodologies with neural intelligence, machine learning, and intelligent automation. It supports continuous, scalable, and context-aware vulnerability.

ASEADOSSDNIoT, a novel and publicly available intrusion detection dataset supported by a fully documented hybrid testbed framework. Framework for spatial selectivity estimation using machine learning and optimizer feedback. Addresses both RCC filters and distance-based filters by transforming estimation into regression task. Compares neural networks, tree-based models and instance-based approaches against traditional RTree and histogram methods across 14 spatial datasets.

A comprehensive machine learning project for credit risk assessment and Expected Credit Loss (ECL) calculation using synthetic loan data. This project implements Basel-compliant credit risk frameworks including Probability of Default (PD), Loss Given Default (LGD), Exposure at Default (EAD), and Expected Credit Loss (ECL) modeling.

It is an intelligent web-based disease prediction system designed to assist healthcare professionals and patients in identifying potential Heart, Lung, and Brain disorders using machine learning models.It provides an easy to use interface where users can input key health parameters, and the system predicts the disease occurrence with high accuracy.

PredNetRSA is a machine learning-based framework for predicting network performance by estimating RSA (Routing and Spectrum Allocation) metrics. NDVI drives prediction, while OpenCV showcases image color and edges, and CNN (MobileNetV2) extracts features for visualization.
